Diagnosis.
Female can be recognised by colour patterns on body (
Fig. 14
), Both sexes with metatarsi and/or tarsi IV dark brown to black (
Figs 15, 16
), other legs yellow-orange. Epigyne with atrium rim very narrow teardrop-shaped; small intromittent orifices open antero-laterally (
Fig. 51
). Male palp RTA with dark, med length, narrow tip (
Fig. 50
); VTA slender, curving at tip (
Fig. 49
).
